<div id="review_1865168876" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1865168876" />
    <a title="Samra Yusuf" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/56939723-samra-yusuf"><img alt="Samra Yusuf" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1584090140p2/56939723.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1865168876?book_show_action=true">Jan 04, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Samra Yusuf" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Samra Yusuf" href="/user/show/56939723-samra-yusuf">Samra Yusuf</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/56939723-samra-yusuf?shelf=asian">asian</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/56939723-samra-yusuf?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1865168876" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6508713176107413479">It is interesting to read historical novels where history is written as fiction.<br/>Here is a novel that tries to record a memorable phase of Indian history through fictional route but the essence is hardly lost in the process.....<br/>We come to know a village at brink of Sutlej that is littered with equal majority of Sikhs and Muslims living together since a long past ago.That is the time of partition, the summer of 1947. Muslims leave India and their exodus to Pakistan is not free from human suffering</span>
  <span id="freeText6508713176107413479" style="display:none">It is interesting to read historical novels where history is written as fiction.<br />Here is a novel that tries to record a memorable phase of Indian history through fictional route but the essence is hardly lost in the process.....<br />We come to know a village at brink of Sutlej that is littered with equal majority of Sikhs and Muslims living together since a long past ago.That is the time of partition, the summer of 1947. Muslims leave India and their exodus to Pakistan is not free from human sufferings.and so is the case with Hindus and Sikhs leaving Pakistan.<br />Story is one very simple in nature if viewed as a love story of a Sikh Scoundrel and a Muslim girl, that ends tragically as the hero sacrifices his own life to save that of her beloved(typical eastern acclaim of "true-love")<br />but,if viewed from a broader canvass,Mano Majra is the one main character that influences the whole lot of events that follows and lead us to other more lucidly placed characters..<br />We come to learn the psyche of A village Magistrate,his convictions and conventions,his conflicts and confusions,his resolutions and improvisations his conscience leaden with sins and his Morales of a saint!<br />And we come to know the head of Sikh temple,Meet Singh naive in manners but very a pacifist in thoughts,his appearance is of a village-dweller but his sayings outwit the so-called western-returned Babu Sahib.<br />Babu Sahib,the spokesman of author,plays a role of a critique,his name alone is an ambivalence for others, He is a rebel, sentimentally attracted to Socialist thinking, but he is primarily concerned with personal leadership. The central quality of Iqbal is that he does not belong anywhere and, what is worse, he pathetically desires to contribute to the mass upsurge of India’s rural committees. When the time comes for his action, he does nothing.(nobody seems to does nothing when needed desperately)<br />Singh has a simple way of telling complicated things,The novel has simple text, not so long-winded in sentence structures, easy to go through and especially lucid for those readers that resist a large mass of text and labyrinthine plots.a dozen more characters,some violence,mindlessness,sex,bigotry,and more violence.<br />But no doubt,author weaves a heart-wrenching story in the backdrop of Partition..<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="6508713176107413479" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


