  <span id="freeText12483369420957965798" style="display:none">With pellucid prose bound to tug the strings of your heart, Khushwant Singh brings to life an India that had just gained Independence. Men stepped out with swords, shielding themselves with religious scriptures, slashing through the good and the bad. Reason took a back seat when men, driven by faith, wiped out entire villages. The despondent waited for death disguised as an old friend, a neighbor or a priest from the house of God. The intellectual ensconced to safety when it dawned upon them that the country they belonged to, by virtue of birth, was not religiously pluralistic.</span>
