<div id="review_3872047166" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3872047166" />
    <a title="Austin George" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/115764833-austin-george"><img alt="Austin George" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1618048409p2/115764833.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3872047166?book_show_action=true">Jul 11, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Austin George" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Austin George" href="/user/show/115764833-austin-george">Austin George</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3872047166" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4386198836791822985">Tragic story about the partition of British India into India and Pakistan, and how it affected the residents of a fictional hamlet in India, Mano Majro, right near the India - Pakistan border. Very well executed story. It got better and better as it approached the climax. As an Indian I wish to visit Pakistan someday, though my ancestors are from South India which is far away from Pakistan, just for the sake of nostalgia. <br/><br/>Some of the Muslims of Pakistan slaughtered the Hindus and Sikhs of Pakist</span>
  <span id="freeText4386198836791822985" style="display:none">Tragic story about the partition of British India into India and Pakistan, and how it affected the residents of a fictional hamlet in India, Mano Majro, right near the India - Pakistan border. Very well executed story. It got better and better as it approached the climax. As an Indian I wish to visit Pakistan someday, though my ancestors are from South India which is far away from Pakistan, just for the sake of nostalgia. <br /><br />Some of the Muslims of Pakistan slaughtered the Hindus and Sikhs of Pakistan, and some of the Hindus and Sikhs of India slaughtered the Muslims of India. The innocent people who were not involved in it had to bear the consequences of these pogroms. Muslims of India had to leave behind their livelihoods, properties and non Muslim friends and forced to run for their lives to Pakistan. Some went willingly with joy and some went unwillingly with broken hearts. Same can be said about the Hindus and Sikhs forced to leave Pakistan. Sometimes I wish there were no religions in this world so that the world lived in peace. But alas this idealist wish of an utopian world exists only in the figment of one's imagination. Humans will find other reasons to fight over - race, ethnicity, language, gender, rich, poor, powerful, weak and so on.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4386198836791822985" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


